<br>
Once there, she had thrown a deep blue cloak over her face, hiding it from strangers, and she stepped off her chariot which had docked at the Athenian shores.  A giant soft white mare waited for her near the coast.  She mounted her giant mare, and was lead off to Athena's temple by more neried servants.<br>
<br>
When approaching the Warrior Goddess's temple, she dismounted and with her deep occulars, she eyed the temple down.  Before her fellow nerieds left, she bid them with a hug and began her way into the temple.  She did not knock, she just melted into a puddle and seeped her way in through all the cracks.  <br>
<br>
Just then, a little drop of herself fell from the roof, and onto the floor making the slightest of sound.  More drops began falling, as if Athena's temple had a leak.  After a few drops had fallen, the floor of Athena's Temple began to slightly flood.  When the water had reached ankle deep, it all began rushing to one spot towards the doors.  As the water began to rise up, it took on the figure of a shapely woman.  <br>
<br>
After all of the water had collected, shaping her, the water began to look more like that of a woman, and then Amphitrite was shown.  Thigh long deep blue tendrils cascading lightly down her back, moving as though it was almost alive, matched her cold deep occulars.  A pale-blue face, shined with a glittery-substance, stared sternly at the Warrior Goddess.  A silken dress, colored like the deep abyss of oceans, fell languidly across her body, and over the dress was her matching cloak.  After she had fully appeared, she brought her two long hands up to the hood of her cloak, and eased it back with her slender and delicate fingers, softly pressing against her locks with her long nails as they passed.<br>
<br>
&quot;Greetings, Athena.  What is it that the Warrior Goddess needs with a Goddess of the Sea?&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goddessamphitrite>Goddess Amphitrite</A> at: 5/7/03 4:03:45 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daughterofshylock>Daughter of Shylock</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 382<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/7/03 8:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=316.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: putting the plot in action</span><hr size=1> Alecto and the other Furies vanished from Amphitrite's sight. <br>
