In a puff of black some, she appeared besides Athena, waved to Auntie Amphitrite and looked to Athena, &quot;don't get all pissy because Im here, I just want to tell you something.&quot; <br>
::She grabbed Athena's arm and brought her down to her so she could wisper in her ear.::  &quot;If your going to try to get her to be against her dear Poseidon, make sure you drill into her head that fact that him and I have had various and many affairs with each other.....&quot;  She grinned:: &quot;And be sure to tell her many of them happened in there own bed, and his throne.&quot; ::She winked to Athena:: <p>{*}In the heart of man lies Eris, Goddess of Discord and Strife, dont try to deny it. {*}</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xgoddessathenax>xGoddess Athenax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Goddess of Wisdom and War</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/8/03 9:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=316.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.hometown.aol.com/amznqyakut1/images/goddessathena1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ohh this is goood...</span><hr size=1> Athena's black orbs gleamed when the Sea Queen arrived. She noted the Furies hiding. The Warrior Goddess offered a seat at the great feasting table just to the side of her throne.<br>
<br>
&quot;Have a seat, dear Amphitrite.&quot;, she smiled letting the sea Goddess only interpert the gesture of kindness and not the true wickedness behind it. When Eris interupted and whispered her knowledge to Athena. Her smile grew wide, and crimson lines coiled over her eyes, like snakes on fire they slithered to her ebony irises before disappearing.<br>
<br>
&quot;Your the light of my life, Eris.&quot;, she whispered back. Athena appreciated any help from the Goddess of discord. The War Queen grinned taking a seat across from Poseidon's wife.<br>
<br>
&quot;I have to tell you something, because all Goddesses of Olympus have to watch each others back.&quot; She glanced to Eris before her attention returned to Amphitrite.<br>
<br>
&quot;Poseidon has been betraying you for a long time. He took Eris into your bed many times, even to his throne. Their affairs have been going on right under your nose.&quot; Athena started to speak but she let the boiling inside her settle.<br>
<br>
&quot;He also conspired with Hephaestus. He tricked the forge God into violating me. Fortunately, he didn't succeed.&quot; She paused letting it sink in. <br>
<br>
Athena sent a word to the Furies, telepathically <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>~&quot;If she doesn't believe me..I ask Tisophone to speak it into the Goddess's ear...Only then would she be insane enough to understand. I will chain her with the chains of Hephaestus and you can bid her pasage to the Underworld. Agreed?&quot;~</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
The Goddess quietly and calmyl waited for Amphitrite's response. <p>_.- Goddess Athena, Goddess of Wisdom, War, the arts, and crafts -._<br>
