<br>
Their words did not change her emotions at all.  She knew of her husband's actions, she was not an ignorant woman.  A cynical look fell across her face as she began to speak.<br>
<br>
&quot;My dear Goddesses, I know of what you speak.  I am not a weak and ignorant Goddess.  I am slightly offended that you would think that.  But I hold nothing against you both, and I do not let the offense get to me.<br>
<br>
You forget, it was Poseidon who wanted me.  I had my eyes on those of my neried race, but him, ruling over the one thing I love, intrigued me.  As long I have my sea, he can have his affairs.  For I know I can not give him all he deserves, especially since I do not love him enough,&quot; she glances at Eris and then back to Athena, &quot;as some women do.  My passion is with the sea, and nothing else.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh, and I am truly sorry for my husband's actions against your will, Athena, but you must understand, he is a man.  And you do have an intriguing air around you.&quot;<br>
<br>
With that, Amphitrite sat back in her chair, awaiting their response. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daughterofshylock>Daughter of Shylock</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 420<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/19/03 5:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=316.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Tisiphone smirked lightly.<br>
